      "instruction": "<p>Once the pastry is almost cooked, heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of<strong> butter</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced spring greens </strong>with the <strong>remaining garlic</strong> and a small splash of<strong> cold water</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until tender – these are your<strong> garlicky greens</strong></p>",
